title: OneTab crashed - lost half my tabs - please help!
content:
I had 16 windows open with around 1400 tabs. I discovered OneTab and it seemed like the answer to my prayers as even 16GB RAM struggling with so many open windows. I managed to close 7 windows and around 700 tabs by using the OneTab list. My whole computer shutdown overnight for a Windows update, and when I re-opened all my Mozilla Firefox tabs popped up as usual. (I have a few crashes here and there and never had a problem restoring tabs with normal Firefox windows.) My single OneTab had the option for 'sessionrestore' but when I clicked it, NOTHING, zero tabs and I am gutted.

1. is there a backup file of what was transferred into OneTab? 2. I have not synced, can I restore my whole Mozilla account to where I was 3 days ago with 16 windows open? 3. There is nothing in recently closed tabs/windows - is the only way to go back through my whole browsing history for the last 6 months and restore that way? 4. I cannot do a full computer system restore as been deleting files and other work - I must find a solution through Mozilla. How can I get back in time?

Anyone able to help or advise? Much appreciated!

title: Remembered Location
content:
I have Privacy & Security set to Strict with Cookies and Site Data deleted when the browser is closed with only 3 sites in the exclusion tab. I also use a VPN to assist with masking and for connections to defined systems and as part of that I will randomly set it to different countries 'because I can'.

I was looking at the website for the current Rugby World Cup (https://www.rugbyworldcup.com) but it was showing the wrong times for the matches. A little digging showed it had remembered my location from some point last week when the VPN was active and set to Iceland.

There is nothing I can find in my browser settings to permit this and I would appreciate pointers to check further since one of the reasons I have set the higher level of restrictions in my browser is to stop this kind of activity from websites.

title: Firefox tarayıcısında oturum bilgilerinin sistem yeniden başlatıldığında silinmesi
content: Firefox tarayıcısını standart modda kullanmama rağmen, bilgisayarımı kapatıp açtığımda giriş yaptığım web sitelerindeki oturumlarım (Google, Microsoft, LLM web siteleri ve geri kalan tüm giriş bilgileri) sona ermiş oluyor. Tarayıcı ayarlarında "geçmişi temizle" özelliğini kapattım, çerezler standart izlemede, Firefox kapanınca çerezleri temizle özelliği kapalı ve gizli mod kullanmıyorum. Tüm ayarların üstünden geçtim. Bu durum çerezlerin sistem kapanışıyla birlikte silinmesine neden oluyor gibi görünüyor fakat aynı zamanda ayarlarda çerezler ve ön bellek 1.4gb yer kaplıyor. Bu davranış varsayılan bir özellikse değiştirilmesini; bir hata ise düzeltilmesini rica ederim.

title: Firefox Not Showing Pages in Search
content: This is a subtle problem. I used to be able to have pages listed in my search history. Now I can only have a search for that page listed. So I have to click on the search result in "Search Facebook" on desktop, click the search for the page in the search history and then click the page in the search results to get to the page. I don't have to do this for groups. Pages have a magnifying glass beside them which they never had before. When I click on any of these, I just get a list of results of searches for posts related to these pages, not the page itself. If I click a group, I go straight to the group with no list of posts. I logged out, cleared the cache and cookie but that didn't solve the issue.
